Federal Paper Board Co Inc saidits is offering 2,800,000 shares, or 140 mln dlrs, of its 2.875cumulative convertible preferred stock at 50 dlrs per share.    The company said it is applying to list the preferred stockon the New York Stock Exchange.    The First Boston Corp, Morgan Stanley and Co Inc andPaineWebber Inc are underwriting the issues, the company said.    The preferred stock has a liquidation preference of 50 dlrsper share and is convertible at any time into common stock at55 dlrs per share subject to adjustment.    The preferred stock is redeemable starting at 52.875 dlrsper share on March 15, 1987, and declining on each March 15 to50 dlrs on and after March 15, 1997.    The company said it intends to used the proceeds from thesale to redeem its entire 125 mln dlrs of its outstanding 13pct subordinated debentures due 2000, with the balance to beadded to the company's general funds. Reuter&#3;